The paper deals with data-stream algorithms, which are typically studied in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of probabilistic methods and the focus on estimation and approximation suggest that the paper could also be relevant to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also mentions heavy-hitter estimation algorithms, which are commonly studied in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with estimating sums and norms, which are topics that fall under the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category.
